File: ocp-ipi-powervc/Oc.go
Line: 135 to 228
Type: potential_issue
Severity: major

Comment:
ClusterStatus has two compounding error-visibility gaps.

1. fmt.Println/fmt.Printf bypass the structured logger (lines 137, 144, 194, 218).
All error text is written to stdout only. In any environment that captures structured log output (log aggregator, systemd journal, CI pipeline), these messages are invisible. Use log.Errorf or log.Warnf consistently — and keep the fmt.Print* calls only if stdout output is an intentional contract.

2. Per-command failures are logged at DEBUG level (lines 195, 219).
When DEBUG logging is disabled (typical in production), a command failure silently disappears from structured logs. Command errors should be logged at Warn or Error level so they surface without needing debug verbosity.

3. The method returns void, so callers cannot react to aggregate failures.
failCount/pipeFailCount are computed but discarded after logging. Consider returning an error (or a summary struct) so callers can take action when critical status commands fail.



🐛 Suggested direction

-func (oc *Oc) ClusterStatus() {
+func (oc *Oc) ClusterStatus() error {
 	if oc == nil || oc.services == nil {
-		fmt.Println("Error: OpenShift cluster object not initialized")
-		log.Debugf("ClusterStatus: Oc or services is nil")
-		return
+		log.Errorf("ClusterStatus: Oc or services is nil")
+		return fmt.Errorf("OpenShift cluster object not initialized")
 	}

 	kubeConfig := oc.services.GetKubeConfig()
 	if kubeConfig == "" {
-		fmt.Println("Error: KUBECONFIG path is empty")
-		log.Debugf("ClusterStatus: KUBECONFIG is empty")
-		return
+		log.Errorf("ClusterStatus: KUBECONFIG is empty")
+		return fmt.Errorf("KUBECONFIG path is empty")
 	}
 	// ...
 	if err := runCommand(kubeConfig, cmd); err != nil {
-		fmt.Printf("Error: could not run command: %v\n", err)
-		log.Debugf("ClusterStatus: Command %d failed: %v", i+1, err)
+		log.Warnf("ClusterStatus: Command %d/%d failed: %v", i+1, len(cmds), err)
 		failCount++
 	}
 	// ...
+	if failCount+pipeFailCount > 0 {
+		return fmt.Errorf("ClusterStatus: %d command(s) failed", failCount+pipeFailCount)
+	}
+	return nil
 }

